execute_now.description: If this field is set to True the specified task will be executed immediately.

automatic_restart.description: Indicates whether there will be an automatic restart when the appliance executes the task.

predecessor_task.description: If this scheduled task has a predecessor task set, its reference will be returned in this field.

approver_comment.description: The comment specified by the approver of the task.

scheduled_time.description: The time when the task is scheduled to occur.

approval_status.description: The approval status of the task.

member.description: The member where this task was created.

execution_time.description: The time when the appliance executed the task.

is_network_insight_task.description: Indicates whether this is a Network Insight scheduled task.

re_execute_task.description: If set to True, if the scheduled task is a Network Insight task and it failed, a new task will be cloned from this task and re-executed.

execution_details.description: Messages generated by the execution of the scheduled task after its completion.

execution_details_type.description: The type of details generated by the execution of the scheduled task after its completion.

dependent_tasks.description: If this scheduled task has dependent tasks, their references will be returned in this field.

submit_time.description: The time when the task was submitted.

execution_status.description: The execution status of the task.

changed_objects.description: A list of objects that are affected by the task.

submitter_comment.description: The comment specified by the submitter of the task.

comment.description: Comment for the Extensible Attribute Definition; maximum 256 characters.

default_value.description: Default value used to pre-populate the attribute value in the GUI. For email, URL, and string types, the value is a string with a maximum of 256 characters. For an integer, the value is an integer from -2147483648 through 2147483647. For a date, the value is the number of seconds that have elapsed since January 1st, 1970 UTC.

list_values.description: List of Values. Applicable if the extensible attribute type is ENUM.

name.description: The name of the Extensible Attribute Definition.

min.description: Minimum allowed value of extensible attribute. Applicable if the extensible attribute type is INTEGER.

max.description: Maximum allowed value of extensible attribute. Applicable if the extensible attribute type is INTEGER.

namespace.description: Namespace for the Extensible Attribute Definition.

descendants_action.description: This option describes the action that must be taken on the extensible attribute by its descendant in case the 'Inheritable' flag is set.

flags.description: This field contains extensible attribute flags. Possible values: (A)udited, (C)loud API, Cloud (G)master, (I)nheritable, (L)isted, (M)andatory value, MGM (P)rivate, (R)ead Only, (S)ort enum values, Multiple (V)alues If there are two or more flags in the field, you must list them according to the order they are listed above. For example, 'CR' is a valid value for the 'flags' field because C = Cloud API is listed before R = Read only. However, the value 'RC' is invalid because the order for the 'flags' field is broken.

allowed_object_types.description: The object types this extensible attribute is allowed to associate with.

type.description: Type for the Extensible Attribute Definition.

comment.description: The global Smart Folder descriptive comment.

query_items.description: The global Smart Folder filter queries.

status.description: Indicate the validity status of this AWS user.

last_used.description: The timestamp when this AWS user credentials was last used.

account_id.description: The AWS Account ID of this AWS user. Maximum 64 characters.

access_key_id.description: The unique Access Key ID of this AWS user. Maximum 255 characters.

secret_access_key.description: The Secret Access Key for the Access Key ID of this user. Maximum 255 characters.

nios_user_name.description: The NIOS user name mapped to this AWS user. Maximum 64 characters.

name.description: The AWS user name. Maximum 64 characters.

comment.description: The personal Smart Folder descriptive comment.

is_shortcut.description: Determines whether the personal Smart Folder is a shortcut.

group_bys.description: The personal Smart Folder groupping rules.

query_items.description: The personal Smart Folder filter queries.

comment.description: Comment for the task group; maximum 256 characters.

grid_member.description: Member on which the tasks in this task group will be run.

account_id.description: The AWS Account ID associated with this task group.

consolidate_zones.description: Indicates if all zones need to be saved into a single view.

sync_status.description: Indicate the overall sync status of this task group.

disabled.description: Indicates if the task group is enabled or disabled.

network_view.description: The name of the tenant's network view.

task_list.description: List of AWS Route53 tasks in this group.

consolidated_view.description: The name of the DNS view for consolidating zones.

name.description: The name of this AWS Route53 sync task group.

status.description: The status of all HSM SafeNet devices in the group.

group_sn.description: The HSM SafeNet group serial number.

pass_phrase.description: The pass phrase used to unlock the HSM SafeNet keystore.

hsm_safenet.description: The list of HSM SafeNet devices.

key_server_ip.description: The remote file server (RFS) IPv4 Address.
